This paper focuses on improving the transaction dissemination protocol in the Bitcoin network, which involves network connectivity, bandwidth usage, and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security and attacks, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as another likely category. The paper proposes a new protocol to improve network efficiency, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis and simulations to evaluate the proposed protocol, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
